doc_summary_long: Attorney General Sessions Rescinds Obama-Era Memo Discouraging Use of Private Prisons The Department of Justice has rescinded guidance from August that discouraged the use of private prisons. 'This will restore (the Bureau of Prison's) flexibility to manage the federal prison inmate population based on capacity needs,' the Justice Department said in a statement.
doc_summary_short: Attorney General Sessions Rescinds Obama-Era Memo Discouraging Use of Private Prisons
doc_title: Attorney General Sessions Rescinds Obama-Era Memo Discouraging Use of Private Prisons
